INPUT province
INPUT gender
INPUT age
IF province==Punjab
THEN
  IF gender==girl
  THEN
    IF age<16
    THEN OUTPUT "marriage not allowed"
    ELSE OUTPUT "marriage is allowed"
    END IF
  ELSE 
    IF age<18
    THEN OUTPUT "marriage not allowed"
    ELSE OUTPUT "marriage is allowed"
    END IF
  END IF
ELSE
  IF age<18
    THEN OUTPUT "marriage not allowed"
    ELSE OUTPUT "marriage is allowed"
    END IF
END IF


My understanding:
if provinve is punjab then check for gender. Check age restrictions acc to gender and output the corresponding result. otherwise the province would be sindh
which has a general age restriction regardless of gender so check only age and output the corresponding result.

